This approach iterates through all available menus to check their status individually.

```python
def IsEnabled(self, *args, **kwargs):
        "check if all top menus are enabled"
        for i in range(self.GetMenuCount()):
            if not self.IsEnabledTop(i):
                return False
        return True
```

The function uses an early exit: it stops and returns False the moment any single menu fails the test, optimizing performance.
